title: Missing M’sian in west Sumatra landslide was travelling to visit relatives
description: KUALA LUMPUR: Malaysian citizen Asrul Nizam Apridwson, 30, who went missing following a landslide in Padang Panjang, West Sumatra, Indonesia on Nov 27, was reportedly on his way to visit relatives there. Read full story
